author: newsroom@capegazette.com (Dan Cook)
title: Cape volleyball defeats solid Saint Thomas More Squad 3-1
text:
Cape volleyball defeats solid Saint Thomas More Squad 3-1 Vikings improve to 10-1 on the season By Dan Cook | Oct 15, 2015 Photo by: Dan Cook The Cape squad leaps with joy after the final kill shot of the 3-1 win over St. Thomas More. 
The Lady Vikings volleyball squad came out of the locker room on fire and won their 10th match of the season with a 25-16, 26-24, 12-25 and 25-22 over St. Thomas More Academy. 
Sophomore setter Logan Shuttleworth assisted on 35 points while senior libero Kira Vitella made 28 digs in the match. Middle blocker Abby E'Nama slammed eight kills, Taylor Collier picked up seven and Alison Palmer and Izzie Marsico each had six kills. 
"I was thrilled with our first set performance," said head coach Tyler Coupe. "I think it was the best we've played all season. We knew St. Thomas More was going to be a strong team from the get go. They pushed us and we responded." 
Cape has never won more than 11 games in a season .They are 10-1 under first year coach Tyler Coupe with 4 left to play. Cape senior captain Kira Vitella serves one of her two aces in the contest. (Photo by: Dan Cook) Cape senior Alison Palmer slams one of her six kills in the match. (Photo by: Dan Cook)
